# Build and Test, See how Mobile Center helps you ship apps faster

# Overview

Mobile Center brings together multiple services, commonly used by mobile developers, into a single, integrated product. You can build, test, distribute, and monitor your mobile apps and easily add backend cloud services to scale your app to millions of users on demand.

# Objectives

- Fork a GitHub project.
- Link a GitHub account with Mobile Center.
- Set up an automated build and test of a mobile project.
- Review build and test results.

# Prerequisites

- A GitHub account ( [http://github.com](http://github.com))

# Intended Audience

This Quick Start Challenge is intended for developers who are familiar with the process of mobile development. It does not require any experience with development itself.

# Task 1: Fork a copy of the demo project

1. Log in to your GitHub account at [https://github.com](https://github.com).
2. Search for the **&quot;myweather.forms&quot;** repo.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. There may be several results. Select the one under **jamesmontemagno**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **Fork** the project into your own account. You now have your own copy to work with.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

# Task 2: Set up a build in Mobile Center

1. Open a new browser tab and navigate to the **Mobile Center** at [https://mobile.azure.com](https://mobile.azure.com).
2. Click **Connect with GitHub**. This is the easiest way to link your accounts so that Mobile Center has access to your projects.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. If this is the first time you&#39;re connecting via GitHub, you&#39;ll be asked to consent to some permissions requests. Click **Authorize application**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Click **Add new app**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Enter **&quot;MyWeather-Android&quot;** as the **Name** of the project and select **Android** and **Xamarin**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. From the left-hand navigation, select the **Build** tab.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **GitHub** option.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **MyWeather.Forms** project.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **master** branch.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Click **Set up branch**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **Release** configuration.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Enable the option to **Sign builds**. As part of this, you&#39;ll need to upload the **Build.keystore** file available in the **C:\Labs** directory under the code for this lab. Both passwords are **&quot;Build\*1234&quot;** and the **Alias** is **&quot;Build2016&quot;**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. If available, select the option to **Start your trial now!**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the option to **Run a lunch test on a device**. This will validate that the build loads as expected. Note that it does take around ten minutes. Also select **Distribute builds** to notify group members when a build becomes available. Click **Finish setup** to kick off the first build.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. It will take some time for the build to complete.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

# Task 3: Review build and test results

1. Once the build has completed, select it.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. You can review the details of the build, including full build output.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **Test** tab.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the most recent test run.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. The test run included only one test, so click **App Launches Test**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. The test review page provides a screenshot of the end of the test, along with defaults on what device was used and information about memory and CPU usage. (Want a free t-shirt? Take a screenshot of this page and follow the instructions at the end of the lab.)

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select the **Distribute** tab and note that one tester (you) are included on the distribution.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. If you check the email associated with your account (probably your GitHub email), you&#39;ll see a new message from **Visual Studio Mobile Center** announcing the new build&#39;s availability. You could then click through to learn more and get the new build.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Want a sweet new **Mobile Center t-shirt**? Take a screen shot of your successful launch test and tweet it out to **#build2017 @MobileCenter**. Then show the booth staff and they&#39;ll hook you up!

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

# Summary

Congratulations on completing this Quick Start Challenge! In this lab, you&#39;ve learned how to use Mobile Center to set up an automated build, test, and distribution workflow—and all in only a few minutes!
